# General Documentation Standards

## README Structure

You must include:
- Project/module purpose
- Key components
- Usage examples (minimal)
- Dependencies (why needed)
- Testing commands
- Links to related docs

You must keep updated:
- Installation steps
- Configuration
- Development commands
- Breaking changes

## Code Comments

You should comment:
- Why, not what
- Business rules
- Workarounds (with TODO)
- Complex algorithms (approach)
- Non-obvious decisions

You must not comment:
- Obvious code
- What code does
- Commented-out code (delete it)
- Outdated information (update or remove)

## TODO Format

You must use:
- `// TODO: Description`
- `// TODO(username): Description`
- `// FIXME: Description`
